# Check both files:
ls -l legacy-data-manager/backend/requirements*.txt

# See contents (first few lines):
head -n 20 legacy-data-manager/backend/requirements.txt 2>/dev/null
head -n 20 legacy-data-manager/backend/requirements.prod.txt 2>/dev/null

# Create requirements.prod.txt file:
cat > legacy-data-manager/backend/requirements.prod.txt <<'EOF'
fastapi
uvicorn[standard]
slack_sdk
google-api-python-client
google-auth
google-auth-httplib2
google-auth-oauthlib
httplib2
sqlalchemy
pydantic-settings
python-dotenv
requests
Pillow
pytesseract
python-docx
python-pptx
openpyxl
pdfminer.six
PyPDF2
EOF

# Install dependencies
pip install -r requirements.prod.txt


## Netify
# 1) Link repository
Click “Link repository”
Choose GitHub → authorize Netlify (if prompted)
Select your org and repo
Pick your branch (use the dropdown) and continue
# 2) Build settings
Base directory: leave blank
Build command: npm run build
Publish directory: legacy-data-manager/frontend/build
# 3) Environment variable
In “Environment variables” → Add variable:
Key: REACT_APP_API_BASE_URL
Value: https://YOUR-BACKEND.onrender.com
Save
# 4) Trigger first deploy
Go to Deploys → “Trigger deploy” → “Clear cache and deploy site”
If you can’t link the repo (org restrictions), use manual deploy:
Locally: cd legacy-data-manager/frontend && npm ci && npm run build
On Netlify: “Add new site” → “Deploy manually” → drag the build/ folder (legacy-data-manager/frontend/build) into the drop zone
Then add REACT_APP_API_BASE_URL in Site settings → Environment variables → redeploy (Clear cache and deploy)


REACT_APP_API_BASE_URL=https://testcleo-backend.onrender.com